  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nThe QML Storybook app has been adopted to the daily basis UI development. It speeds up both creating new components and maintenance existing ones and also fosters better isolation. However there is no good mechanism to prevent from regressions. There is automatic checker for Storybook pages but it validates only if given page is compilable.\r\n\r\nTo address that problem the idea is to allow defining qml unit tests directly in the Storybook's pages or provide other mechanism of close integration of storybook and unit tests. An argument in favor of this solution is the fact that Storybook provides a stub mechanism and many mock models that could be easily reused in unit tests.\r\n\r\nThe purpose of this task is to collect ideas and explore possibilities. \r\n",
